WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.937
Every WashCentral screen carries the same tools in the top-right corner.

p02
00:00:04.347 --> 00:00:06.118
They follow you from page to page.

p03
00:00:06.747 --> 00:00:08.304
Three of them do the daily work:

p04
00:00:08.528 --> 00:00:12.880
jumping anywhere, focusing the view, and asking questions in plain language.

p05
00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:14.773
Press Control K.

p06
00:00:15.879 --> 00:00:19.899
The command palette opens dead center, cursor already blinking.

p07
00:00:20.168 --> 00:00:22.116
It's the quickest way to any page.

p08
00:00:22.417 --> 00:00:26.400
Rather than hunt through menus, you picture where you're headed and type it.

p09
00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:27.739
Now, the results.

p10
00:00:27.739 --> 00:00:31.545
Search reads the whole platform, not just page titles.

p11
00:00:31.545 --> 00:00:35.533
Each hit names where you'll land and the module it lives under,

p12
00:00:35.533 --> 00:00:38.038
so the palette quietly teaches you the layout.

p13
00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:41.151
Watch the footer, then tap the arrow keys.

p14
00:00:41.556 --> 00:00:45.826
The highlight moves with each press.

p15
00:00:46.189 --> 00:00:47.035
The palette runs entirely from the keyboard:

p16
00:00:47.322 --> 00:00:49.549
arrows to move, Enter to open, Escape to back out.

p17
00:00:49.972 --> 00:00:51.166
Build the habit early.

p18
00:00:51.701 --> 00:00:52.398
Press Escape.

p19
00:00:52.398 --> 00:00:56.807
The palette closes and drops you back exactly where you were,

p20
00:00:56.807 --> 00:00:59.370
without opening or changing a thing.

p21
00:00:59.370 --> 00:01:01.113
Closing Search is always safe.

p22
00:01:01.576 --> 00:01:03.406
Now click the location selector.

p23
00:01:03.910 --> 00:01:07.532
By default it reads All Locations, your whole network.

p24
00:01:08.098 --> 00:01:11.878
This control decides which sites your dashboards and numbers come from.

p25
00:01:12.347 --> 00:01:14.612
Right now, that's every wash you run.

p26
00:01:15.109 --> 00:01:16.162
Underneath, two lists.

p27
00:01:16.162 --> 00:01:20.152
One groups sites by state, with a count beside each.

p28
00:01:20.152 --> 00:01:23.046
The other drills into a single wash.

p29
00:01:23.046 --> 00:01:26.376
Pick either, and every dashboard narrows to match.

p30
00:01:26.376 --> 00:01:30.102
For support work, remember: it only changes your view.

p31
00:01:30.102 --> 00:01:35.367
The data never moves, and one click back to All Locations restores the whole network.

p32
00:01:35.889 --> 00:01:37.770
Click the selector again to close it.

p33
00:01:38.836 --> 00:01:42.300
We browsed and picked nothing, so scope stays on the full network.

p34
00:01:43.013 --> 00:01:46.852
Scanning the list never filters a thing until you actually choose.

p35
00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:48.116
Last tool.

p36
00:01:48.116 --> 00:01:49.398
Click Ask Shyne.

p37
00:01:49.398 --> 00:01:52.411
Shyne is the assistant built into WashCentral.

p38
00:01:52.411 --> 00:01:56.242
Ask it about customers, operations, or marketing in plain language,

p39
00:01:56.242 --> 00:01:58.390
and it pulls the answer together.

p40
00:01:58.900 --> 00:02:01.945
The Try Asking prompts give you a feel for its range.

p41
00:02:02.715 --> 00:02:04.289
Payment declines at one site, prepaid members gone quiet,

p42
00:02:04.746 --> 00:02:06.358
last week's damage claims, VIPs at risk of leaving.

p43
00:02:06.857 --> 00:02:15.600
If that's a question you'd normally dig through reports for, try Shyne first.

p44
00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:18.904
At the bottom, a question box and a Send button.

p45
00:02:19.733 --> 00:02:22.544
Normally you'd type a question here and Shyne would answer.

p46
00:02:22.745 --> 00:02:23.941
We won't send one today.

p47
00:02:24.849 --> 00:02:27.047
What matters is the line just below:

p48
00:02:27.307 --> 00:02:31.002
the answer is AI-generated, so verify it before you act.

p49
00:02:31.745 --> 00:02:35.414
Treat Shyne's reply as a fast first draft you always confirm.

p50
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:36.981
Click Close.

p51
00:02:37.612 --> 00:02:42.480
The window disappears with no question sent, your workspace right where you left it.

p52
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.103
So that's the header.

p53
00:02:44.507 --> 00:02:47.525
From any screen, Control K jumps you anywhere,

p54
00:02:47.816 --> 00:02:50.993
the location selector focuses the view without touching a record,

p55
00:02:51.282 --> 00:02:55.053
and Ask Shyne answers your questions, as long as you verify first.

p56
00:02:55.473 --> 00:02:57.096
Three tools, one corner.

p57
00:02:57.413 --> 00:03:01.039
Learn them now, because every lesson ahead assumes you can reach them.

